OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Bill
OL,4,CGladdon
OL,6,FHe'd originally trained with the Royal
OL,7,FWest Kents in Maidstone as gunner,
OL,8,Fwireless operator, and driver before
OL,9,Fpassing out as a despatch rider and
OL,10,Fthen joining the airborne assault.
OL,12,FHe was dropped near the River Orne
OL,13,Fwhere the Allies secured two bridges
OL,14,Fto stop the Germans destroying them
OL,15,Fand holding up the advance.
OL,17,FHe said: "We waited and at last we
OL,18,Fwere off. I had the inside of the
OL,19,Fglider up my back and a tank near to
OL,20,Fme. That was my unorthodox landing in
OL,21,FNormandy.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/6
