OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Bill
OL,4,CGladdon
OL,6,FHe landed east of the River Orne and
OL,7,Fwas told to dug in for the first
OL,8,Fnight. Pegasus Bridge and the Orne
OL,9,FBridge had been take.
OL,11,FThen he went to Ranville where his
OL,12,Fcolleagues made a camp in an orchard,
OL,13,Fgoing out daily on recce missions.
OL,15,FMr Gladdon was in Normandy for 12 days
OL,16,Fbefore being shot in the ankle.
OL,18,FHe said: "We had come back to the
OL,19,Forchard and I was just going to boil
OL,20,Fsome water and have a brew up.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/6
