OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Bill
OL,4,CGladdon
OL,6,F"Suddenly there was a bang and I was
OL,7,Fon the ground. I didn't know what had
OL,8,Fhappened.
OL,10,F"I was carried to a barn where we put
OL,11,Four wounded. In fact two days prior to
OL,12,Fthem taking me I carried two of my
OL,13,Fmates over. They were dead by the time
OL,14,Fwe got them over. They are in Ranville
OL,15,Fcemetery now.
OL,17,F"And they started pumping the morphine
OL,18,Finto me and I went out. I was wounded
OL,19,Fon the 18th and they kept me in a
OL,20,Fhospital there for three days and then
OL,21,FI came back (to England).
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/6
